RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6F Turf CR: 95. Claiming Purse 34000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS OR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THUNDERHEART was away well then pressed the pace from inside, took over with three furlongs remaining, shook free from outer rival around the bend, drifted out then back inward in the lane and stayed clear to the wire. LANSDOWNE (GB) stalked the top pair from off the rail, rounded the bend three wide, took aim at the winner in the lane but could not summon the needed rally. BEAUDACIOUS stalked four wide into the turn, spun three wide into the lane, could not find the late response to challenge in the furlongs grounds but churned on to hold the show. FRANKLIN ONE STAR stumbled leaving the gate, jumped the dirt crossing then began to pull the rider along to the turn, got boxed in while along the fence around the bend, moved out to a clear path in the lane and finished with a mild rally. MENDEZ MILE broke a step slow, stalked from inside through the turn, tipped out in upper stretch and failed to rally. PETRUCHIO dropped back under coaxing early, traveled three then two wide on the turn, steered out in the lane and also lacked a rally. TANGLEDUPINGREY stumbled leaving the gate, lost path and steadied shortly after, ran up on heels and had to put the brakes on once again, ran two wide through the turn and weakened. BLACK MAGICIAN set the pace while pulling the rider along up the backstretch with THUNDERHEART to the inside, was overtaken by that rival at the three-eighths pole, could not keep up approaching the quarter pole and chased two wide leaving the bend and weakened in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Franklin One Star
ENTRY.OWNER: Boat Racing LLC Pony King Dube Abraham O'Neill Shane and Strauss William
ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled, jumped xing, pulled, boxed in, mild rally

ENTRY.NAME: Thunderheart
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed inside, cleared turn, moved out upper

ENTRY.NAME: Mendez Mile
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, stalked inside, tipped out, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 22000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOT ROD MAMA chased four wide into the first turn then went up to duel outside MIDNIGHT SILENCE on the backstretch, battled two wide through the far turn and into the stretch, disposed of the runner-up outside the eighth pole and drew away. MIDNIGHT SILENCE broke a step slow then went up to vie for command three wide while keen around the first turn, dueled inside HOT ROD MAMA up the backstretch and far turn, could not keep up approaching the furlong grounds but stayed on to secure second. JACQUELINE COCHRAN forwardly placed from the rail into the first turn then lost her path when DEL MAR WOMAN came in a bit around the bend, moved off the inside to give chase through the middle stages, rounded the far turn two wide and lacked a late bid. AMERICAN CONQUEST chased five wide early, started to weaken three then two wide on the second bend and continued to weaken in the lane. DEL MAR WOMAN stumbled leaving the gate then went up to vie for command in the two path under coaxing, could not keep pace with the leaders and chased up the backstretch, began to weaken along the rail on the far turn and had little left for the drive. TAP IN NINE trailed three wide around the first turn, trailed four wide into the stretch and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Jacqueline Cochran
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost path 1st, stalked inside, angled out, chased 2wide, no bid

ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, keen 3wide 1st, dueled inside, no match late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 3 6F Turf CR: 77. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IRISH PATSY broke a step slow and came in at the start, sat off the pace in the two path leaving the backstretch, gained two then three wide around the bend, took over at the furlong pole, then quickly cleared and inched away. PRECIPICE broke slow, chased two wide off the pace around the bend, angled out in upper stretch, finished in tandem with PAID IN GOLD and edged that rival for the place. PAID IN GOLD bobbled leaving the gate, stalked the pace inside MISS POLO BAR into the turn, got shuffled back when that rival came over on the turn, continued along the fence to the drive, then steered out and finished determinedly but lost the photo for second. SOUL OF A WARRIOR stalked the leader from inside then moved out a bit, rounded the bend in the two path, reached the front briefly in upper stretch before being overtaken by the winner at the eight pole and flattened to fourth. ELEGANCE CODE broke well then dropped back off the pace and steered inward, navigated the turn two wide, moved out in the lane and improved position. MISS POLO BAR tracked two wide outside a rival into the turn, moved over to the rail around the bend, got blocked behind a weakening PRETTY RENA at the top of the lane, then gained a clear path but could not regain momentum. CRESCENDO MOLTO was off a bit slow to start, trailed two to three wide around the bend, drifted out in the lane and never got involved. PRETTY RENA cleared early and crossed over, set the pace along the rail to the lane and retreated when overtaken in upper stretch.

AWESOME TAYLOR broke a step slow, moved up to press the leader from outside early, chased three wide into the turn, two wide into the stretch and kept on to best the rest. MODERA stalked from outside early, rounded the bend four wide, failed to threaten in the lane but finished a clear third. THE REIGN SONG got crowded a bit between rivals early, tracked outside a foe into the turn, went three then two wide around the bend and could not rally. DADDY CLASSY DILL coaxed along from the gate then drifted out early, chased two wide through the bend, moved out in the lane and could not rally. QUICKLIKEABUNNY tracked two wide into the turn, moved over to the rail while losing ground on the turn and lacked further response in the drive. MISS KALINE was rank briefly trailing the field, went four to five wide around the bend and weakened.

SILENT HEAT lost his footing and broke slow from outside, chased two wide early then had to steady around the first turn, had to steady again at the nine-sixteenths pole, asked two wide on the far turn and lacked a bid. STAN FROM MALIBU sped to the front in the two path, got pressured around the first turn, vied inside a pair into the second bend while losing command, started to retreat around that turn, eased in the lane and walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CATALINA EDDY was closest in pursuit of the leader from outside in the two path, bid two wide into the far turn, led briefly into the stretch before being overtaken giving the lead back to BOSS SULLY, bumped with that rival at the eighth pole, continued to battle and drifted inward to bumped again in the final sixteenth and dug in late to prevail. OLD PAL bobbled slightly leaving the gate, stalked in the two path early, bid three deep late on the far turn and flattened in the final furlong. TOM AND JAZZY had to steady behind BOSS SULLY early, was rated along the rail after, saved ground to the stretch and lacked the needed response when called upon.
